w modes of existence. At once a corrective to the predominantly white male accounts of the AIDS crisis and an openhearted depiction of the possibilities of black gay life, Evidence of Being above all insists on the primacy of community over loneliness, and hope over despair.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfrican American gay menzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aAfrican American gay menzWashington (D.C.) 0aAfrican American gay menzWashington (D.C.). 0aAmerican literaturexAfrican American authors. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aAIDS.  aCultural Arts Movement.  aHIV.  aNew York City.  aWashington, D.C.  ablack gay men.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226589961423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226589961/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles